The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Malaria count in House
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Malaria count in House
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	More than 24,000 people were affected with malaria and four         
	died in 51 wards of the Calcutta Municipal Corporation (CMC) this year, urban development minister Asok Bhattacharya said in the Assembly on Thursday.        
	According to our estimates, 24,837 people were affected with malaria till October. Around 8,500 suffered from malignant malaria. Four of them died, the minister said.        
	Three of the 166 people who were affected with dengue this year died.... Instances of such tropical diseases are increasing in urban areas.        
	The minister informed the House that the government would try to set up malaria clinics in all 141 wards in the city. Now, 85 wards have such clinics where blood samples can be tested. We will try to open such clinics in all 141 wards. Mosquito repellents are being sprayed in the city and a house-to-house campaign has been launched to spread awareness about preventive steps, the minister said.                                                                                                                                                                         
